UNITED STATES ex rel. John James PANNONE, Relator-Appellant, v. Laureat L. MARTINEAU, United States Immigration Inspector in Charge, Respondent-Appellee. No. 61. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 15, 1937. Robert H. Alcorn and Thomas R. Robinson, both of New Haven, Conn., for appellant. Robert P. Butler, U. S. Atty., of Hartford, Conn., for appellant.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
